SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 797
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to commend and congratulate Caden Baugh of
Greeneville High School upon receiving the
2025 Tennessee Titans Mr. Football Award for
Division I, Class 4A.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those outstanding young athletes who, through their superlative efforts and
achievements in high school football, have distinguished themselves as true champions of the
sport; and
WHEREAS, one such remarkable individual is Caden Baugh, a senior at Greeneville
High School who was recently honored with the 2025 Tennessee Titans Mr. Football Award for
Division I, Class 4A; and
WHEREAS, a two-year starter for the Greene Devils, Mr. Baugh becomes the fifth
individual in program history to receive the honor; and
WHEREAS, during his senior year, Caden Baugh completed 122 of 159 passes for
2,653 yards and 36 touchdowns, garnering him the fourth most yards and the third most passing
touchdowns in a single season in Greeneville High School history; and
WHEREAS, the stellar senior also rushed for 1,152 yards and 14 touchdowns during his
final season, all while proving himself to be the ultimate team player and leading the Greene
Devils to the 4A semifinals—the ninth such appearance in program history—finishing just one
game shy of the state championship and posting a 12-2 season record; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Baugh is a winner both on and off the field of play, and his dedication to
excellence is clearly deserving of the respect, admiration, and commendation of this General
Assembly; now, therefore,
SJR0797
011739
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and congratulate Caden
Baugh of Greeneville High School upon receiving the 2025 Tennessee Titans Mr. Football
Award for Division I, Class 4A and extend to him our best wishes for his every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
